1. What is responsible for defining the routes of the games resource?
server/server.js and server/helpers/create_router.js

2. What do you notice about the folder structure? Whats the client responsible for? Whats the server responsible for?
The client has the Container and Components which has the logic for hoe the page works
The server holds the db details and hte game routes

3. What are the the responsibilities of server.js?
It holds the url and details of the DB

4. What are the responsibilities of the gamesRouter?
it sets the base url to keep code DRY

5. What process does the the client (front-end) use to communicate with the server?
src/services/GamesService.js which holds functions to look at the url used and has logic for each requirement

6. What optional second argument does the fetch method take? And what is it used for in this application? Hint: See Using Fetch on the MDN docs
Custom settings like GET and POST methods


7. Which of the games API routes does the front-end application consume (i.e. make requests to)?
The database

8. What are we using the MongoDB Driver for?
To connect to the node.js app